subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Males of 

A. coccineus

can be distinguished from other congeners by the black and slender embolus with a truncated tip (E; 
Fig. 2A
). Females can be separated from other members of the genus by an anteriorly wide epigynal septum (Se; 
Fig. 2D, F
) (see 
Schmidt & Scharff (2008)
for a proper differential diagnosis).
